  "prompt": "What is the processing time for Australian Visa 190?",
  "response": "The processing time for the Australian Visa 190 (Skilled Nominated visa) can vary significantly and is difficult to predict with certainty. It depends on several factors, including:\n\n*   **Demand:** The number of applications received.\n*   **Completeness of the Application:** Complete applications with all required documents are processed faster.\n*   **Skill Occupation:** Certain occupations may be prioritized.\n*   **State Nomination:** Processing times can vary between different states and territories.\n*   **Individual Circumstances:** Factors like health and character checks.\n*   **Policy Changes:** Changes to immigration policies or procedures.\n\n**Where to Find the Most Up-to-Date Information:**\n\nThe official source for the most up-to-date processing times is the **Australian Department of Home Affairs website.**\n\n1.  Go to the Department of Home Affairs website ([https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/](https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/)).\n2.  Search for \"visa processing times\".\n3.  Look for the page related to \"Visa processing times\".\n4.  Find the Skilled Nominated visa (subclass 190).\n5.  Review the information.  They often provide estimates based on recent visa grants (e.g., \"75% of applications processed in X months\" and \"90% of applications processed in Y months\").\n\n**General Expectations (Keep in mind this is a broad generalization, ALWAYS check the official website):**\n\nHistorically, processing times can range from several months to over a year.  It's not uncommon to see estimates like:\n\n*   75% of applications processed in 6-12 months.\n*   90% of applications processed in 12-18 months (or longer).\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **These are estimates, not guarantees.**  Your application could take longer.\n*   **Check the official website regularly for updates.** Processing times can change.\n*   **Ensure your application is complete and accurate** to avoid delays.\n*   **Be patient.** Visa processing takes time.\n\nIn summary, while I can't give you a precise timeframe, the Department of Home Affairs website is the best place to find the most current estimates for Visa 190 processing times.  Check there regularly and factor in the variables mentioned above.\n",
